  <abstract>Option for purchase of land from Margaret Shute and Leila Shute Tigert drafted by the United States War Department for "Berry Hill's Air Crew Classification Center". The property sold was 22.75 acres "between the L. &amp; N. Railroad line, Decatur Division, the Radnor Yards, and South of Thompson Lane" and the purchase price was $3400.</abstract>
  <abstract>Leila (1868-1952) and Margaret (1857-1948) Shute were two of the four daughters of William and Lavinia Shute. Both sisters lived at Grassmere, managing the family farm after their father died. The property in this document, near Harding Place and Trousdale Lane, became an Air Crew Classification Center used for training air corps personnel during WWII.</abstract>
